      <Fragment slot="technical">
        <p class="font-bold text-lg text-navy-900 mb-3">Technical summary:</p>

        <p class="font-bold text-navy-900 mt-4 mb-2">Scope:</p>
        <p class="mb-3">A 1,525-line PRD specifying a permissioned blockchain-based voter verification layer. Verification-only — sits alongside existing election infrastructure. Buildable blueprint: architecture, data schemas, threat models, cost models, rollout phases, and 14 open questions.</p>

        <p class="font-bold text-navy-900 mt-4 mb-2">PII boundary:</p>
        <p class="mb-3">Strict separation between <strong>identity enrollment plane</strong> (SSA, USCIS, state vital records) and <strong>verification plane</strong> (VoteChain). The chain never ingests PII. DID-to-PII linkage only in state-operated encrypted vaults, accessible by court order. Architectural invariant, not a policy promise.</p>

        <p class="font-bold text-navy-900 mt-4 mb-2">Architecture:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2.5 mb-4">
          <li><strong>Consortium chain</strong> (Hyperledger Fabric-class): 74-node BFT — 6 federal, 50 state, 12 auditor, 6 oversight. Category-quorum: 3-of-4 categories, &ge;2/3 intra-category.</li>
          <li><strong>Identity:</strong> W3C DIDs with voter-held private keys. zk-SNARKs prove all five attestation pillars without disclosing identity.</li>
          <li><strong>Data model:</strong> Per-state channels + one national channel for nullifier dedup. Target: 10,000+ TPS, &lt;3s finality.</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="font-bold text-navy-900 mt-4 mb-2">Five verification pillars:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2.5 mb-4">
          <li><strong>Citizenship:</strong> 2-of-4 source attestation at enrollment, DID-bound, 10-year expiry.</li>
          <li><strong>Eligibility:</strong> Per-election smart contract — age, residency, judicial status, registration.</li>
          <li><strong>Liveness:</strong> Biometric (local match, never centralized) or non-biometric first-class path. &lt;48h death-record revocation SLA.</li>
          <li><strong>Duplicate Prevention:</strong> One-time nullifier = hash(DID + election_id). Cross-state real-time detection.</li>
          <li><strong>Chain-of-Custody:</strong> Device DIDs with HSM attestation co-sign events.</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="font-bold text-navy-900 mt-4 mb-2">Fraud detection:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2.5 mb-4">
          <li><strong>Synchronous:</strong> Nullifier collision, invalid ZKP, compromised device, geographic impossibility.</li>
          <li><strong>Asynchronous:</strong> Death matching, judicial drift, enrollment anomaly clustering, rate-limit violations.</li>
          <li><strong>Flag lifecycle:</strong> Detected &rarr; Triaged &rarr; Investigated &rarr; Resolved (immutable on-chain).</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="font-bold text-navy-900 mt-4 mb-2">Cost &amp; rollout:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2.5 mb-4">
          <li>Baseline: ~$870M capex, ~$375M/yr opex. High-risk: $3.0-4.0B / $0.7-0.9B/yr.</li>
          <li>Phases: Governance (M1-12), POC (M1-6), hardening (M6-24), pilots (M24-36), federal (M36-60).</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="font-bold text-navy-900 mt-4 mb-2">Open questions (14):</p>
